            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Vim modified the behavior of `'modified'` to respect `buftype=prompt` in [vim/vim@4551c0a](https://github.com/vim/vim/commit/4551c0a9fcdbdef52836d4852686d54b5e47fdaf), solely for the termdebug plugin.\n> \n> We could consider breaking with upstream on this and making `buftype=prompt` always ignore `'modified'` as it did before that commit\n\nYes let's do this. In fact this was part of my todo list in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34561 : \n\n> editing a prompt marks the buffer as \"modified\", this is usually just unwanted and annoying",
